===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|㓞|大|ls=psc|ls2=ic|c1=p|c2=s|t1=to engrave|t2=person}}, hence a person making an agreement and/or carving something with a knife.

Possibly a variant of {{zh-l|*栔}} or vice versa, given that the two characters were used interchangeably in ancient text.

